        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 13 at 6:25PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 624 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Turner, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph, heavy rainfall and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Rainfall up to a half inch is possible in less than 20 minutes as
this storm moves through. Some minor flooding is possible in poor
drainage areas.

Locations impacted include...
Turner and Hogeland.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Heavy rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
